OL,3,CJersey's plan to ban new fossil fuel
OL,4,Cboilers pushed back indefinitely
OL,6,FAn environmental pledge to ban the
OL,7,Finstallation of new fossil fuel
OL,8,Fboilers in from 2026 has been scrapped.
OL,10,FThe aim had been for people to switch
OL,11,Fto greener options such as electric
OL,12,Fboilers under the Government's that
OL,13,Fsets out steps to reach net-zero
OL,14,Femissions by 2050.
OL,16,FHowever, Jersey's Environment
OL,17,FMinister, Deputy Steve Luce, announced
OL,18,Fthat the ban had been delayed
OL,19,Findefinitely.
