OL,3,CJersey's plan to ban new fossil fuel
OL,4,Cboilers pushed back indefinitely
OL,6,FHe said: "Putting back the ban on
OL,7,Freplacement fossil fuel boilers isn't
OL,8,Fa cancellation of the policy but is a
OL,9,Fsignal that we're reprioritising some
OL,10,Fof this work to make sure it's done in
OL,11,Fthe right order, at the right time."
OL,13,FIn an email to ministers seen by ITV
OL,14,FNews, Deputy Luce explained: "I am
OL,15,Fconcerned that the industry does not
OL,16,Fhave the staff or expertise to install
OL,17,Flow carbon heating at the rate that
OL,18,Fwould be required if the ban on
OL,19,Freplacing fossil fuel boilers in
OL,20,Fexisting buildings was to come into
OL,21,Feffect in 2026.
